truth: Hey, Iris.
iris: O-oh—Truth. H-hey...
truth: [color=#e85670][i]She flinches a little. Not from me… just from being seen.[/i]
truth: [color=#e85670][i]Iris was always like this.[/i]
truth: [color=#e85670][i]Timid, almost careful. It was like if she stayed small enough, nothing would see her.[/i]
truth: What’ve you been up to?
iris: N-nothing much... just... resting, I guess.
truth: [color=#e85670][i]Her eyes don’t stay on me. They drift—past me, around me.[/i]
truth: Quiet day?
iris: Y-yeah... it's just...
iris: The house feels kinda... empty now.
truth: Empty?..
truth: ...Yeah. I guess it does.
truth: I don't know... everything's just... in place. 
iris: U-um... well, a clean home is a clean heart, right?
truth: ...
truth: Yeah.
truth: Something like that.
[signal arg="iris_intro_complete"]